title: Injury report: Safety Trenton Robinson sprains ankle and thumb in loss to Jets
text:
By Liz Clarke October 18 at 7:38 PM Follow @lizclarketweet Jets wide receiver Eric Decker, left, avoids a tackle by Redskins safety Trenton Robinson. (Seth Wenig/Associated Press) 
The Redskins came away from Sundayâ€™s 34-20 loss to the New York Jets with few injuries. 
Safety Trenton Robinson left the game with a sprained left ankle and sprained thumb and did not return to the game. He was in a walking boot in the locker room afterward. 
Running back Chris Thompson, who was slow to get up after taking a hard fall after leaping in vain for a ball thrown well over his head, was diagnosed with a back sprain. It was a frightening moment in the game, given that the 5-foot-8 Thompson had broken his back while at Florida State. Thompson also had a team-high six catches. 
Cornerback Bashaud Breeland played on despite a bruised knee. 
And Ty Nsekhe, filling in for left tackle Trent Williams, who is undergoing concussion monitoring, left the game briefly with a foot injury but returned.
